#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/automation/cronie.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "GNU/Linux provides the *cron* system, which is a time-based `cron` jobs program for automated processes. It is not hard, but quite powerful. Want a script or program to run at 5 pm every day? `cron` can do it. There are different branches (or variants) of `cron`, which have the same functions. In this document, **cronie** is used, and the version is 1.5.2. You can click [here](https://github.com/cronie-crond/cronie) to find the latest version and update log.\n"
